<TITLE> BNP's Mahmudur sues AL's Imam for defamation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 28 (bdnews24.com)  Former BNP energy adviser Mahmudur Rahman filed a defamation case against Awami League election committee co-chairman HT Imam on Sunday. Imam told a briefing at the AL media centre on Saturday that newspaper owner Mahmudur Rahman, along with two former inspectors general of police and the personal secretary of Jamaat-e-Islami leader Ali Ahsan Mojaheed, had been "training 100 people for the last one month" on preparing fake ballots and loading them into boxes. Imam had said they were also printing counterfeit ballots after collecting samples from the government press to this end. According to Mahmudur's suit the allegations amount to defamation and a "personal attack". Mahmudur petitioned the Dhaka chief metropolitan magistrate's court in the afternoon for an arrest warrant against Imam. Newspaper owner Mahmudur filed the case with the Dhaka court Sunday morning. Judge Abdul Kajid recorded the statement of the plaintiff in the afternoon and ordered the investigation officer of Dhanmondi police station to submit his report by Feb 11. Mahmudur mentioned in his petition that Awami League election committee co-chairman HT Imam made false and insulting allegations about him in a press conference at the AL media centre on Saturday. The BNP leader told the court that he was not associated with any such activities. He said Imam's statement was defamatory, a personal attack and made him insecure. bdnew
